OL,3,CThames Water discovers 312 storm
OL,4,Coverflows it didn't know it had
OL,6,FWater companies are permitted to dump
OL,7,Fsewage in "exceptional" circumstances.
OL,8,FStill, Ofwat has decided that Thames
OL,9,FWater has been doing so routinely
OL,10,Fsince 2017 because it has failed to
OL,11,Fproperly manage its network of sewers
OL,12,Fand treatment works.
OL,14,FSome 39% of Thames Water's storm
OL,15,Foverflows "spill" more than 20 times a
OL,16,Fyear - the level the regulator
OL,17,Fconsiders to be excessive.
OL,19,FIn 2020, it was 49%.
