OL,6,FMany of the plants are not running at
OL,7,Fcapacity because of what the regulator
OL,8,Fsays is a combination of human error
OL,9,Fand equipment that is either poorly
OL,10,Fmaintained or needs replacing.
OL,12,FWater companies have faced a series of
OL,13,Fregulatory and legal actions since it
OL,14,Fbecame clear that they have been
OL,15,Freleasing unknown quantities of
OL,16,Fwastewater into national waterways,
OL,17,Fputting the environment and human
OL,18,Fhealth at risk.
